# Page Plan: Enrollment — Document Signing

## Route
`/enrollment/documents`

## Purpose
Hosts the document signing step (Step 3 of 3 — optional) of the Enrollment Checklist. Completing this step finalises enrollment and transitions the user to `Student`.

## Roles Permitted
- `Applicant` with approved application, `tuitionPaid === true`, and `quizPassed === true`.
- Redirect to `/enrollment` if `documentsSigned === true`.
- Redirect to `/enrollment/quiz` if `quizPassed === false`.

## UI Layout

1. **Enrollment step header** — "Step 3 of 3: Sign Documents" + back link to `/enrollment`.
2. **Step progress bar** — consistent across all enrollment step pages.
3. **Document signing UI** — see `ai/forms/08-document-signing.mdc`:
   - Scrollable `react-markdown` render of `public/documents/code-of-conduct.md`.
   - Typed name field + agreement checkbox.
   - "Sign & Complete Enrollment" button.

## Data Requirements
- `enrollments.getOwnEnrollment()` — verifies step preconditions on load.
- `enrollments.signDocuments({ typedName })` — marks step complete, triggers role promotion.
- `users.promoteToStudent(userId)` — called internally within the mutation on full completion.

## Navigation
- On successful signing → `/student/dashboard` (with a congratulations message).
- Back link → `/enrollment` checklist overview.
